  "text": "3) Comparison to Previous Work: To the best of our knowledge, besides [CITATION_1] , which was written concurrently and independently from our work, [CITATION_2] is the only published RNN adversarial attack up to date. [CITATION_3] is somewhat similar to our proposed attack, specified in section III-B. The differences from this paper, as mentioned in section II-D-4, are: 1) Our attack is black-box, not white-box. 2) We don't modify existing API calls to prevent damage to the malware functionality. However, we want to compare our attack to previous work in terms of performance, that-is, in terms of effectiveness (Definition 3) and overhead (Definition 4).",
